HEADWORD: Fourch
<hw>Four`ch⟦eacute⟧"</hw> <pr>(f⟦oomac⟧r`sh⟦asl⟧")</pr>,
<pos>a.</pos> <ety>[F. See <er>Fork</er>.]</ety> <fld>(Her.)</fld>
<def>Having the ends forked or branched, and the ends of the branches
terminating abruptly as if cut off; -- said of an ordinary, especially
of a cross.</def>⟦br⟧
